parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS light and brake light come on simultaneously
the ABS system fails to operate
the brakes fail to respond
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking
and the brakes make a loud squeaking noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle can cause loss of control, accidents, and leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Abnormal sounds
vibrations
or noises coming from the rear of the vehicle
rear wheel rubbing against the wheel well
loss of control
and sudden failure of the rear axle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion and Rusting of Rear Axle
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and rusting of the rear axle can cause the axle to fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, and leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Rust or corrosion on the rear axle
abnormal sounds
vibrations
or noises coming from the rear of the vehicle
and sudden failure of the rear axle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Repair of Rear Axle under Recall
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate repair of the rear axle under recall can cause the axle to fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, and leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Failure of the rear axle after recall repair
abnormal sounds
vibrations
or noises coming from the rear of the vehicle
and sudden failure of the rear axle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety-critical systems to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Intermittent failure of wipers
headlights
radio
windows
door locks
and other electrical systems; ABS and brake lights coming on and off; speedometer and other gauges malfunctioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to lose critical information about the vehicle's speed, leading to accidents or traffic violations.
symptoms: Speedometer
tachometer
gas gauge
temperature gauge
and other instruments malfunctioning or giving incorrect readings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: ABS and brake lights coming on and off; erratic braking behavior; loss of traction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sliding door can cause injury or entrapment.
symptoms: Sliding door not staying shut; door malfunctioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting of the subframe can cause structural damage to the vehicle, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Rusting of the subframe; hole in the subframe behind the front driver-side wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle will not shift into gear
the transmission fluid leaks
the O/D light flashes
and the check transmission light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle can cause the wheel to separate from the vehicle, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: The rear axle cracks or breaks
the vehicle makes a loud noise while driving
the wheel wobbles or vibrates
and the vehicle loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake and ABS systems can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The ABS light comes on
the brake light comes on
the brakes feel soft or spongy
and the vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical and instrument panel systems can cause the vehicle's systems to malfunction, leading to accidents or inconvenience.
symptoms: The interior lights flash or do not work
the cruise control does not engage or disengage
the gear shifter is loose or hard to shift
and the speedometer does not work properly.
